{
  "text": ", while pebble samples yield rates ranging from~0.02 to 0.54 mm yr À1 (Table 2 ). Uncertainties Figure 7b ). When comparing results for a single catchment, pebbles generally (with only one exception) yield higher mean erosion rates compared to sand (Figure 7b ). Two previously published sand samples taken from near the Humahuaca Basin outlet yielded erosion rates of 0.038 ± 0.006 mm yr À1 (sample STR-21) and 0.055 ± 0.008 mm yr À1 (sample STR-24) [CITATION_1] . Those rates are similar to the three bedrock erosion rates, which range from 0.038 ± 0.006 to 0.061 ± 0.008 mm yr À1 (2σ, Table 2 and Figure 7b ).",
